WEBVTT

00:46.379 --> 00:49.007
I'm running tirelessly.

00:51.801 --> 00:54.095
I'm sprinting at full speed.

00:57.140 --> 00:58.099
But…

00:59.225 --> 01:01.186
I don't know where I'm headed.

01:06.149 --> 01:08.151
I must be at school this time.

01:13.239 --> 01:15.241
The closer I get to my classroom,

01:16.242 --> 01:19.537
the more certain I become…

01:23.458 --> 01:27.921
that as always, the door will be locked.

01:30.840 --> 01:34.302
Sir, I'm not in class.
Please open the door!

01:34.385 --> 01:35.470
Sir!

01:36.721 --> 01:38.223
Open the door for me!

01:38.890 --> 01:40.642
Can you not hear me?

01:40.725 --> 01:43.186
COUNSELOR'S OFFICE
SOPHOMORE CLASSROOMS

01:45.688 --> 01:47.649
-Answer sheets, please.
-Please let me in!

01:47.732 --> 01:50.360
Open the door!

01:51.236 --> 01:52.737
Please open the door!

01:55.782 --> 01:57.325
Do you not hear me?

02:27.480 --> 02:28.648
This must be how men feel

02:28.731 --> 02:31.818
when they have dreams
of getting dragged back into the military.

02:41.286 --> 02:44.664
Please do not run, play around,
or lean sideways on the escalator.

02:59.053 --> 03:01.264
The train is approaching.

03:07.353 --> 03:09.105
The doors are now closing.

03:09.188 --> 03:11.774
The screen doors are now opening.

03:12.358 --> 03:14.777
The destinations in my dreams can vary.

03:15.403 --> 03:20.575
It could be school, work,
or a university entrance exam room.

03:23.286 --> 03:25.079
The places may vary,

03:25.580 --> 03:29.083
but it always ends the same way.

03:34.047 --> 03:35.757
I'm always abandoned

03:36.966 --> 03:38.927
outside of a closed door.

03:59.072 --> 04:02.075
Hello, I'm Lee Yeo-reum
from Planning Team One.

04:03.284 --> 04:05.870
Hello, I'm Lee Yeo-reum
from Planning Team One.

04:06.537 --> 04:08.456
Handwritten poems.

04:08.539 --> 04:11.292
Poems are drafted not only using logic…

04:14.212 --> 04:16.422
THE EMOTIONS WILL BE FELT..

04:23.096 --> 04:25.014
Were you rehearsing?

04:25.723 --> 04:28.184
Are you already experienced enough
to submit proposals?

04:28.268 --> 04:30.144
"Handwritten poems."

04:30.687 --> 04:32.355
The theme of the project is…

04:32.438 --> 04:34.023
Kind of old-fashioned, right?

04:34.107 --> 04:35.316
Is everyone ready?

04:37.443 --> 04:38.403
This one is important.

04:40.947 --> 04:43.032
You don't look so terrible today.

04:44.742 --> 04:45.868
I'll call the CEO then.

04:45.952 --> 04:47.412
Mr. Choi.

04:47.495 --> 04:49.664
This may not be so important, but…

04:49.747 --> 04:50.957
What? Don't make me nervous.

04:51.040 --> 04:54.544
I heard the new CEO is extremely picky.

04:54.627 --> 04:56.587
He doesn't drink just any kind of coffee.

04:57.422 --> 05:00.341
Do you think this
cheap canned coffee would do?

05:00.967 --> 05:02.468
-Really?
-Yes.

05:03.052 --> 05:05.763
He only drinks some fancy coffee
called Geisha or something.

05:05.847 --> 05:07.140
Hold on.

05:08.099 --> 05:10.810
-What was it called?
-Geisha.

05:13.604 --> 05:14.564
Ms. Lee.

05:15.815 --> 05:17.734
Were you not aware?

05:17.817 --> 05:20.278
-I'm sorry.
-I mean…

05:20.862 --> 05:24.032
Isn't it your job to find out
what your superiors like?

05:24.115 --> 05:26.117
Should I go buy some right now?

05:26.200 --> 05:28.536
Hurry it up. I can't stall for long.

05:30.288 --> 05:31.581
Are you seriously walking?

05:59.317 --> 06:00.860
Could I get Geisha coffee?

06:34.811 --> 06:36.062
…handwritten poems.

06:36.145 --> 06:39.482
Next is the concept of the project.

06:39.565 --> 06:41.275
As you can see on the slide,

06:41.359 --> 06:46.531
each poem illustrates
the poet's character, emotions,

06:46.614 --> 06:49.700
and their surroundings at the time.

06:50.409 --> 06:53.371
For example, the poet Shin Dal-ja…

06:55.623 --> 06:57.208
was immersed in her surroundings,

06:57.291 --> 07:01.254
so it's easy for the readers to understand
the poem was written for her lover.

07:01.337 --> 07:03.881
Like this, handwritten poems contain

07:03.965 --> 07:07.927
retrospective feelings
and heartfelt emotions that printed poems…

07:09.262 --> 07:11.097
That was great.

07:11.180 --> 07:13.057
Until now, we were only focused on

07:13.141 --> 07:16.144
making a profit by investing well.

07:16.227 --> 07:20.815
But a retro-themed project
in times like these?

07:22.108 --> 07:23.734
It's fantastic. I was touched.

07:23.818 --> 07:24.986
Thank you.

07:25.069 --> 07:26.946
We've got a long way to go
until we're on your level.

07:27.572 --> 07:31.909
Why don't we take this project
a step further and do one for each poet?

07:32.660 --> 07:33.619
Thank you so much.

07:34.203 --> 07:35.913
-Thank you.
-We'll do our best, sir!

07:35.997 --> 07:37.540
Let's all go have lunch together.

07:37.623 --> 07:39.500
-Shall we go?
-Sure.

07:40.668 --> 07:42.253
A brilliant idea, right?

07:42.336 --> 07:43.379
Indeed.

07:43.463 --> 07:46.090
You were amazing.
It was like you prepared the project.

07:46.883 --> 07:47.884
Mr. Choi.

07:49.552 --> 07:52.805
You see, he came in
immediately after you left.

07:52.889 --> 07:54.932
-We were all so rattled.
-Indeed.

07:55.516 --> 07:57.852
While you were getting coffee,

07:57.935 --> 08:01.063
Ms. Kim here stepped in
and managed to finish the job.

08:01.898 --> 08:03.524
Great work.

08:03.608 --> 08:06.861
It's going to be a lot of work
for Da-mi to clean up by herself.

08:06.944 --> 08:07.987
That's true.

08:08.988 --> 08:11.699
-I'll stay behind and help.
-Really?

08:11.782 --> 08:14.285
Then make sure you have lunch, okay?

08:15.119 --> 08:17.663
Thank you for the coffee. Good work.

08:34.430 --> 08:35.806
Hello?

08:35.890 --> 08:36.724
Hey.

08:37.475 --> 08:38.643
Hey, Mom.

08:38.726 --> 08:39.560
Are you busy?

08:39.644 --> 08:42.271
Not really. It's lunchtime.

08:42.355 --> 08:44.857
Is something wrong?
Why do you sound so down?

08:46.067 --> 08:47.193
Nothing's wrong.

08:48.110 --> 08:49.070
Why did you call?

08:49.153 --> 08:51.781
I wanted to send you some dishes
with stir-fried anchovies.

08:51.864 --> 08:53.157
You're out of kimchi, right?

08:53.241 --> 08:54.659
Should I send some of that too?

08:54.742 --> 08:56.244
I have some left.

08:56.327 --> 08:58.037
You haven't finished it yet?

08:58.120 --> 09:00.540
You should eat well.

09:00.623 --> 09:01.916
And try not to eat out.

09:01.999 --> 09:04.669
Okay, I can take care of myself.

09:04.752 --> 09:06.546
All right.

09:06.629 --> 09:07.713
Sorry for nagging.

09:09.590 --> 09:12.218
Do you need anything?

09:12.969 --> 09:14.887
I'll get it for your birthday.

09:14.971 --> 09:17.765
You don't have to come. Birthday, my foot.

09:17.848 --> 09:19.350
I'll just buy whatever then.

09:20.101 --> 09:20.935
Oh, right.

09:21.894 --> 09:24.522
Are your knees feeling better?

09:24.605 --> 09:27.525
They're fine.
They only hurt for a bit back then.

09:27.608 --> 09:30.236
Don't work at the restaurant anymore.
You promised.

09:30.319 --> 09:31.237
Of course.

09:31.320 --> 09:33.864
Hey, are you done washing the cabbages?

09:33.948 --> 09:35.950
-Come and take a coffee break.
-Okay.

09:36.033 --> 09:37.660
You're working again, aren't you?

09:37.743 --> 09:38.744
Gosh.

09:38.828 --> 09:41.539
I don't want to keep you from eating.
I'll call you later.

09:46.335 --> 09:48.879
Why is she working
at the restaurant again?

10:08.524 --> 10:10.151
I told you I'm working late.

10:10.234 --> 10:11.777
You didn't have dinner, right?

10:12.862 --> 10:15.197
You love the sushi from this place.

10:16.282 --> 10:18.117
You didn't have to do this.

10:19.827 --> 10:22.705
You have to get back to work, right?

10:28.628 --> 10:30.421
-One more beer, please.
-Okay.

10:30.504 --> 10:33.799
I sprinted next to the cars on the street
with coffees in my hands.

10:33.883 --> 10:35.760
But I wasn't scared at all.

10:35.843 --> 10:39.221
Then I finally arrived at the office
with the coffee,

10:39.722 --> 10:42.266
only to hear that
the CEO doesn't drink coffee.

10:43.100 --> 10:47.063
Da-mi says that
Ms. Kim tricked me on purpose.

10:47.146 --> 10:48.397
Do you think that's true?

10:48.898 --> 10:49.982
Well…

10:51.108 --> 10:54.862
What you want to know is

10:54.945 --> 10:58.407
if they were lying to you, right?

10:59.033 --> 11:00.951
Yes. That's right.

11:01.452 --> 11:02.745
Okay, how about this?

11:04.205 --> 11:06.040
Let's say that they lied to you.

11:06.624 --> 11:07.708
Why?

11:07.792 --> 11:08.959
Why would they do that?

11:09.877 --> 11:12.046
It's such an obvious lie you'll notice.

11:12.713 --> 11:14.590
-I know.
-So why?

11:15.257 --> 11:17.468
Why do they treat you like some pushover?

11:17.551 --> 11:18.969
Let's think about it.

11:20.262 --> 11:23.224
Do you really think
you don't have any fault in this?

11:23.307 --> 11:24.225
Jae-dong.

11:24.308 --> 11:27.228
Also, the real issue here isn't the lie.

11:29.438 --> 11:31.440
It's the fact that you stayed outside.

11:33.484 --> 11:36.737
Imagine you entered that room with coffee,
soaked in sweat.

11:37.279 --> 11:38.823
The CEO would have been pleased.

11:39.740 --> 11:44.286
You would have won him over
had you gone in and done the presentation.

11:45.037 --> 11:46.497
Do you understand, Yeo-reum?

11:47.915 --> 11:48.916
Yeo-reum. This…

11:49.959 --> 11:52.336
The lie isn't the issue here.

11:53.963 --> 11:56.006
The issue is your complacent attitude.

12:05.558 --> 12:06.642
What now?

12:11.147 --> 12:12.982
Are you offended by what I said?

12:14.817 --> 12:17.194
You've always enjoyed giving me advice.

12:18.028 --> 12:19.113
But…

12:20.739 --> 12:25.578
you didn't use to get this worked up
giving me advice.

12:27.163 --> 12:28.622
Yeo-reum. I…

12:30.749 --> 12:32.835
I'm not angry right now.

12:33.461 --> 12:35.212
It's not that I'm angry.

12:38.466 --> 12:40.050
I'm just a bit tired of you.

12:46.974 --> 12:48.017
Jae-dong.

13:01.489 --> 13:05.075
I've been dating him
for six years since university.

13:06.994 --> 13:09.663
We both changed as time went by.

13:10.247 --> 13:14.752
And I've been obsessing over
marriage for some time.

13:17.505 --> 13:21.091
I'm sure my obsession made him sick of me.

13:23.219 --> 13:27.223
HEY, I'M SORRY FOR BEING A NUISANCE
WHEN YOU'RE SO BUSY…

13:30.601 --> 13:33.562
I PROMISE IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN

13:39.693 --> 13:41.529
I shouldn't have gone to see him today.

13:56.168 --> 13:59.505
YEO-REUM, LET'S TAKE A BREAK FOR A WHILE

14:04.426 --> 14:07.012
WHAT DO YOU MEAN BY THAT?

14:12.434 --> 14:14.144
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN

14:14.228 --> 14:16.981
I THINK IT'S FOR THE BEST.
LET'S TALK AGAIN LATER.

15:15.915 --> 15:17.708
Jae-dong hasn't called since then.

15:19.752 --> 15:22.796
We've had fights like these
in our six-year relationship.

15:23.714 --> 15:26.133
But Jae-dong always
called me first the day after.

15:26.216 --> 15:27.426
Ms. Lee.

15:29.553 --> 15:30.554
Ms. Lee!

15:32.973 --> 15:33.849
Yes?

15:33.933 --> 15:35.309
What are you doing?

15:35.392 --> 15:36.852
Mr. Choi is calling you.

15:39.188 --> 15:40.147
Yes.

15:42.650 --> 15:43.901
Come on in.

15:44.443 --> 15:47.988
It's been about four years
since you started working here, right?

15:48.572 --> 15:50.866
Yes. Four years and three months.

15:50.950 --> 15:52.493
I see.

15:53.661 --> 15:56.705
You must be eager to do more, right?

15:59.249 --> 16:00.960
Is that why you're doing this?

16:04.505 --> 16:08.634
We've only worked with
Joosung print shop until now,

16:08.717 --> 16:11.220
and we pay them 100 million won
for their service.

16:11.303 --> 16:13.472
That's right. Keep going.

16:14.515 --> 16:17.559
I looked into other print shops,
and they had newer printers

16:17.643 --> 16:19.561
and asked for 80 million won for the job.

16:19.645 --> 16:21.647
I see. 80 million won.

16:21.730 --> 16:24.066
That means we'd save 20 million, right?

16:28.195 --> 16:29.196
Ms. Lee.

16:30.155 --> 16:32.449
Do you know why I hired you?

16:33.701 --> 16:34.785
Do you?

16:35.869 --> 16:38.789
To be frank, you're not really
the sly type like Ms. Kim.

16:39.790 --> 16:42.626
How should I put this…

16:43.377 --> 16:47.423
Obeying your superiors
and working like a dog.

16:48.132 --> 16:49.758
That's your strength.

16:50.968 --> 16:54.179
Small companies like ours
don't have an established system,

16:54.263 --> 16:56.640
so you have to stick to
what you're good at.

16:57.433 --> 17:00.436
That's why I want you
to stick to your strengths,

17:00.519 --> 17:02.980
carrying out your tasks quietly
like an obedient dog.

17:04.106 --> 17:05.315
What do you think?

17:06.734 --> 17:09.862
Who are you to change
the fucking print shop on your own?

17:09.945 --> 17:10.946
Tell me.

17:12.823 --> 17:13.657
What?

17:13.741 --> 17:16.243
Did you think
this was your chance to act out

17:16.326 --> 17:17.786
because the CEO liked your work?

17:17.870 --> 17:19.413
No, sir. I'm sorry.

17:19.496 --> 17:21.832
Gosh, your ambition scares me.

17:22.666 --> 17:23.792
Ms. Lee.

17:25.919 --> 17:28.505
If this place was the military,
do you know what you would be?

17:29.548 --> 17:33.052
A military dog. You're not even human.

17:33.635 --> 17:38.098
So please stop racking your brains
with the things you weren't told to do.

17:41.310 --> 17:43.979
Man, this is exhausting.

18:17.429 --> 18:18.806
I'm starving.

18:46.542 --> 18:48.168
Why always me?

19:09.731 --> 19:10.816
Hello?

19:15.779 --> 19:18.407
EMERGENCY ROOM

19:23.203 --> 19:24.746
Don't forget your credit card.

19:27.457 --> 19:31.044
EMERGENCY ROOM

19:39.678 --> 19:41.597
-Yeo-reum!
-Hey!

19:46.935 --> 19:48.478
What do we do now?

19:49.354 --> 19:50.606
Where's Mom?

19:50.689 --> 19:54.818
I was drinking and fishing with my friend

19:54.902 --> 19:56.069
when the cops called…

19:56.153 --> 19:58.155
I'm asking you where she is!

19:59.698 --> 20:00.782
She's…

20:01.366 --> 20:03.535
Come see where she is.

20:13.462 --> 20:20.469
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

20:53.919 --> 20:55.337
Is this your mother?

21:04.554 --> 21:05.639
Mom.

21:11.228 --> 21:12.104
Mom.

21:36.962 --> 21:38.088
Mom.

21:45.137 --> 21:46.722
Mom.

21:47.889 --> 21:49.016
Yeo-reum.

21:51.518 --> 21:52.769
You should sleep.

21:53.812 --> 21:57.774
We have to wake up early
to go visit your dad in the morning.

21:58.400 --> 21:59.568
Mom.

22:00.277 --> 22:03.905
I still sniff garlic whenever I miss you.

22:04.865 --> 22:06.283
Why would you do that?

22:07.951 --> 22:11.246
You used to come home so late
from the restaurant,

22:11.830 --> 22:14.374
that I was always asleep by then.

22:15.292 --> 22:17.919
Your hand smelled like garlic

22:18.628 --> 22:20.922
when you came in to pat my head.

22:27.429 --> 22:28.597
I'm sorry.

22:30.766 --> 22:32.726
Why are you sorry?

22:33.810 --> 22:36.563
There's someone else who should apologize.

22:37.773 --> 22:38.940
Do you mean Dad?

22:39.566 --> 22:42.694
If I meet him again,
I won't let him off easy.

22:42.778 --> 22:45.363
-What will you do?
-For starters,

22:46.281 --> 22:48.408
I won't lift a finger around the house

22:49.367 --> 22:50.952
and I'll stay in bed all day.

22:51.787 --> 22:53.330
And I don't know.

22:53.413 --> 22:55.290
I'll make him do all the hard work.

22:59.419 --> 23:00.462
Mom.

23:02.047 --> 23:04.758
I'll do all of that for you.

23:05.759 --> 23:07.844
I'll make a fortune

23:07.928 --> 23:12.974
so you can go see flowers
and go to the beach.

23:13.058 --> 23:14.643
I'll make that happen.

23:17.562 --> 23:19.856
So don't grow old too quickly, okay?

23:35.247 --> 23:36.373
Yeo-reum.

23:37.332 --> 23:38.416
Yes?

23:39.501 --> 23:40.669
I love you.

23:42.045 --> 23:43.213
I love you too.

23:47.884 --> 23:49.094
Mom…

23:50.053 --> 23:52.180
never got the rest she wanted.

24:48.445 --> 24:50.030
You don't have to see me out.

24:53.617 --> 24:55.160
Thank you for coming.

24:55.744 --> 24:56.786
It's nothing.

24:57.579 --> 24:59.623
I didn't know if you would come.

25:01.750 --> 25:03.627
I can't believe she passed like this.

25:05.837 --> 25:07.088
It must be tough.

25:09.716 --> 25:11.676
I'm sorry I can't be with you.

25:17.098 --> 25:18.391
Stay with her until the end.

25:20.936 --> 25:22.562
Try to eat and sleep

25:24.564 --> 25:26.274
whenever you can find the time.

25:28.735 --> 25:29.778
Okay?

25:34.074 --> 25:35.492
Hang in there, Yeo-reum.

25:38.286 --> 25:39.746
You'll get through this.

25:55.637 --> 25:58.223
I'll get going then.
You should head back in.

26:14.322 --> 26:17.575
And just like that, everyone left.

26:22.372 --> 26:24.833
I rested Mom beside Dad.

26:27.210 --> 26:30.964
She's probably with him by now,

26:31.047 --> 26:33.216
making him work to his bone
to her satisfaction.

26:36.428 --> 26:37.721
At least…

26:38.763 --> 26:39.973
I hope she is.

26:59.784 --> 27:02.579
TO LEE YEO-REUM

27:46.164 --> 27:47.374
My baby.

27:48.375 --> 27:51.086
You sound so blue lately.

27:52.712 --> 27:54.714
You don't have to visit for my birthday.

27:55.382 --> 27:57.550
I hope these home dishes
will cheer you up.

27:59.302 --> 28:00.428
I love you.

28:02.180 --> 28:03.306
Sincerely, Mom.

28:22.784 --> 28:24.869
Mom.

28:31.334 --> 28:33.670
Mom.

28:42.095 --> 28:44.264
I'm so sorry, Mom.

28:51.479 --> 28:53.648
I go to work.

28:57.068 --> 28:59.487
And then I get off work.

29:01.197 --> 29:02.365
Going to work.

29:05.910 --> 29:07.287
Getting off work again.

29:10.707 --> 29:11.833
Going to work.

29:13.042 --> 29:14.169
Getting off work.

29:16.546 --> 29:18.006
Going to work again.

29:23.636 --> 29:27.849
I'm still holding onto my life,
trying not to break down.

29:33.730 --> 29:36.733
Ms. Lee. Could you type any louder?

29:37.525 --> 29:39.778
I can't work with all that noise.

29:39.861 --> 29:41.029
I'm sorry.

29:42.363 --> 29:44.741
Ms. Lee. Wash my mug.

29:47.744 --> 29:49.662
Hurry. My arm's hurting.

29:54.626 --> 29:56.628
Nothing has changed.

29:57.754 --> 30:01.966
Perhaps nothing even happened.

30:20.860 --> 30:22.946
The same sun goes down every day.

30:30.537 --> 30:32.330
And the same sun comes up.

30:37.210 --> 30:39.754
The world is exactly the same.

30:47.929 --> 30:50.682
Except that I've lost my parents.

30:58.106 --> 31:01.985
This stop is Samseong.

31:02.569 --> 31:05.405
The doors are on your right.

31:07.740 --> 31:08.741
Samseong.

31:11.452 --> 31:12.704
Hold on.

31:12.787 --> 31:14.664
Excuse me, mister.

31:14.747 --> 31:16.374
Please stop!

31:19.377 --> 31:21.921
Damn it. What the heck is this?

31:22.005 --> 31:24.674
Talk about a crappy morning.

31:25.967 --> 31:27.635
What a nuisance.

31:28.428 --> 31:30.513
Mister!

31:30.597 --> 31:32.348
Please do not run, play around,

31:32.432 --> 31:34.642
or lean sideways on the escalator.

31:59.626 --> 32:03.755
HI, MR. CHOI. I THINK I'M GOING TO BE
ABOUT 20 MINUTES LATE…

32:37.455 --> 32:39.874
-It's spring.
-The screen doors are now opening.

32:50.510 --> 32:53.221
The train will now be departing.
The doors are closing.

33:08.778 --> 33:10.446
I'm not going to work.

33:47.150 --> 33:49.360
MANAGER CHOI JI-WON

34:04.333 --> 34:08.046
The morning train that goes
in the opposite direction of Seoul…

34:10.048 --> 34:12.884
was relaxing, quiet, and peaceful

34:13.718 --> 34:18.264
as if it was a completely different world.

34:39.494 --> 34:42.747
Perhaps that's what life is.

34:44.123 --> 34:47.627
If I go in the opposite direction
as everyone else,

34:48.503 --> 34:52.006
perhaps life will be more relaxing, quiet,

34:53.174 --> 34:54.634
and peaceful.

35:13.194 --> 35:14.362
I must be out of my mind.

35:17.323 --> 35:18.825
The charger.

35:18.908 --> 35:20.701
Goodness.

35:23.913 --> 35:26.415
14 MISSED CALLS
MANAGER CHOI JI-WON

35:26.999 --> 35:28.167
Oh, right.

35:29.252 --> 35:31.087
I decided not to go to work.

35:34.632 --> 35:37.176
INCOMING CALL
MANAGER CHOI JI-WON

35:40.847 --> 35:41.931
Hello?

35:42.014 --> 35:44.976
Hey, where are you?
Have you lost your mind?

35:45.476 --> 35:47.145
Why the hell won't you pick up?

35:47.770 --> 35:48.896
Mr. Choi.

35:50.815 --> 35:53.901
Just how do you expect
to continue to work here now?

35:57.655 --> 36:01.117
I'm sorry, but I'm quitting.

36:01.659 --> 36:03.411
What? What are you…

36:27.435 --> 36:30.479
Yeo-reum. You really had me worried.

36:30.563 --> 36:32.231
Are you really quitting?

36:33.941 --> 36:35.693
How am I going to survive without you?

36:36.569 --> 36:38.154
You'll be fine, Da-mi.

36:38.696 --> 36:41.449
-Da-mi, can you photocopy this for me?
-Sure.

36:44.160 --> 36:45.411
Ms. Lee.

36:45.494 --> 36:47.288
Can I see you for a moment?

36:57.006 --> 36:58.132
Goodness.

36:58.883 --> 37:01.928
How can you quit so abruptly like this?

37:03.262 --> 37:05.389
Are you getting married or something?

37:06.224 --> 37:07.433
No.

37:08.017 --> 37:10.478
Come on. Make yourself at home.

37:10.561 --> 37:12.271
Why are you awkwardly standing there?

37:12.355 --> 37:13.481
Have a seat.

37:13.564 --> 37:15.608
I've been too harsh lately, haven't I?

37:15.691 --> 37:19.612
I sometimes tend to get overzealous.

37:20.863 --> 37:21.864
Ms. Lee.

37:22.823 --> 37:25.159
I'm saying this not as a manager,
but as a friend.

37:27.119 --> 37:31.207
Believe it or not,
I also graduated from a lousy university.

37:32.708 --> 37:34.835
But I managed to become the team manager,

37:34.919 --> 37:37.129
although I studied engineering
at a lousy school.

37:37.713 --> 37:39.423
How do you think I managed?

37:39.507 --> 37:41.634
It wasn't easy.

37:41.717 --> 37:44.804
I had to grovel before my seniors,
running all kinds of chores.

37:44.887 --> 37:47.682
Compared to back then, you have it easy.

37:48.516 --> 37:50.226
So what I'm saying is

37:50.977 --> 37:53.771
that this isn't the right time
for you to rest.

37:53.854 --> 37:54.772
He's right.

37:54.855 --> 37:56.691
Sure, a short break could be nice,

37:56.774 --> 37:58.859
but you'd have to look for work again.

37:58.943 --> 38:02.154
Ms. Lee. Put your trust in me.

38:02.238 --> 38:03.656
You know I have your back.

38:03.739 --> 38:07.451
So just stick with me,
and it'll be smooth sailing for you.

38:07.535 --> 38:08.619
Okay?

38:09.161 --> 38:11.372
I appreciate you saying that.

38:11.455 --> 38:13.666
-No need to thank me.
-But…

38:15.251 --> 38:17.461
I'm still going to quit.

38:23.342 --> 38:26.304
I have an appointment with the CEO,

38:26.387 --> 38:29.265
so I'll get going.

38:29.348 --> 38:30.808
Ms. Lee.

38:32.643 --> 38:35.688
Don't you fucking understand
what I'm trying to tell you?

38:37.982 --> 38:39.275
You're leaving?

38:39.817 --> 38:41.610
I see. You want to leave.

38:43.195 --> 38:44.196
Go ahead and try.

38:44.280 --> 38:46.324
Let's see what you're capable of.

38:46.407 --> 38:47.700
Mr. Choi.

38:47.783 --> 38:51.787
I tried to keep you around
because you're so subservient.

38:51.871 --> 38:54.832
Kids these days don't know
what it means to persevere.

38:54.915 --> 38:56.751
I feel disgusted to be born

38:56.834 --> 38:59.503
in the same generation
as someone like her.

39:01.630 --> 39:02.631
Fuck you.

39:06.010 --> 39:07.136
"Fuck you"?

39:08.971 --> 39:10.348
Did you just say that to me?

39:10.973 --> 39:12.141
Ms. Lee.

39:14.435 --> 39:17.146
No one in this world
could put up with you.

39:20.316 --> 39:22.985
Why should I put up with
your abuse when I'm quitting?

39:23.069 --> 39:25.946
Don't be like that.

39:26.030 --> 39:28.949
He's only doing this for you.

39:29.533 --> 39:31.202
For me?

39:31.994 --> 39:33.245
That's not true.

39:34.747 --> 39:36.665
His only concern is

39:37.249 --> 39:39.794
that I don't tell the CEO
about him pocketing the rebate.

39:39.877 --> 39:40.795
What did you say?

39:46.092 --> 39:47.635
You!

39:48.135 --> 39:50.429
Are you trying to start a fight?

39:50.513 --> 39:52.056
-You little…
-Stop.

39:52.139 --> 39:53.474
Stop it.

39:55.101 --> 39:56.352
Apologize.

39:56.936 --> 39:58.437
Are you insane?

39:58.521 --> 40:00.022
Both of you.

40:00.106 --> 40:01.315
You must be crazy.

40:01.899 --> 40:03.984
You got 20 million won
from Joosung, right?

40:04.485 --> 40:06.904
You're afraid that I'll tell
the CEO about it.

40:06.987 --> 40:08.823
You crazy bitch.

40:09.407 --> 40:11.826
Fine. Let's go see the CEO together then.

40:11.909 --> 40:13.411
Wait.

40:14.120 --> 40:16.038
Hey. Get a grip.

40:16.122 --> 40:17.581
Why are you acting like this?

40:17.665 --> 40:20.418
You get a grip, Ms. Kim.

40:21.001 --> 40:23.587
He asks all the female employees
to come with him to bars,

40:23.671 --> 40:25.297
-karaoke, and motels.
-Shut up!

40:25.381 --> 40:27.800
He went for you because I rejected him.

40:27.883 --> 40:28.801
What?

40:30.177 --> 40:32.930
Are you seriously saying
that I came on to you?

40:33.013 --> 40:35.724
She's totally nuts.

40:35.808 --> 40:37.435
You want me to show her your texts?

40:38.102 --> 40:40.604
-What? Is this true?
-What texts?

40:40.688 --> 40:42.398
What a conniving bitch.

40:42.982 --> 40:44.567
-What the hell?
-You believe her?

40:44.650 --> 40:46.360
She's lying!

40:47.278 --> 40:48.946
The CEO is looking for Yeo-reum.

40:49.029 --> 40:50.406
I get it already!

40:51.949 --> 40:53.325
-What texts?
-She's lying.

40:53.409 --> 40:54.994
-Show me.
-I told you she's lying.

40:55.077 --> 40:56.495
-Give me your phone.
-I told you she's lying.

40:56.579 --> 40:57.621
Give it. Where is it?

40:57.705 --> 40:59.790
-Wait.
-Where the hell is it?

40:59.874 --> 41:00.958
Hold on.

41:01.584 --> 41:03.752
Let's all calm down.

41:04.336 --> 41:05.337
Do I…

41:05.838 --> 41:08.466
Do I just need to apologize?

41:09.216 --> 41:12.178
I'm sorry. I must have lost my…

41:12.720 --> 41:15.347
I apologize. Please let this one slide.

41:17.558 --> 41:20.311
I don't care what you two are up to.

41:22.146 --> 41:24.815
But you should at least
refrain from harming others.

41:24.899 --> 41:28.569
I will.

41:55.221 --> 41:56.388
Excuse me.

41:56.472 --> 41:58.933
Could you open the gate for me?

42:00.935 --> 42:02.019
Thank you.

42:06.899 --> 42:09.777
I've been living in a daze.

42:11.779 --> 42:13.531
I tried so hard to not fall behind

42:14.281 --> 42:16.158
and to not be mistreated

42:16.867 --> 42:18.661
as if my life depended on it.

42:20.746 --> 42:22.289
But looking back, 

42:23.207 --> 42:25.584
the one who's been mistreating me the most

42:26.085 --> 42:28.921
was myself.

42:39.932 --> 42:42.851
How big did you say your potato field was?

42:42.935 --> 42:45.062
I only planted 1,000 pyeong.

42:45.145 --> 42:47.273
He planted 2,000 pyeong.

42:47.356 --> 42:49.066
That's a lot.

42:49.149 --> 42:51.986
You need at least 1,000 pyeong
to call it a potato farm.

42:52.069 --> 42:54.405
But it's not raining much these days.

42:56.073 --> 42:58.033
They're getting all dried up.

42:58.617 --> 43:00.828
I know, but we can't do anything about it.

43:24.935 --> 43:28.939
YEONGJU TRANSPORTATION

43:34.403 --> 43:36.864
My monthly salary was 2.38 million won.

43:38.198 --> 43:40.993
That's the amount I exchanged my time for.

43:43.287 --> 43:46.165
Now I've decided to use that time

43:47.458 --> 43:50.127
entirely for myself.

44:01.263 --> 44:06.101
You know I'm not the type
that trusts someone easily with a job.

44:06.727 --> 44:09.647
So think of this as an opportunity

44:10.147 --> 44:12.566
and give it your best.

44:12.650 --> 44:13.734
Good luck.

44:13.817 --> 44:14.693
Wait.

44:14.777 --> 44:17.613
I think Ms. Kim was in charge of this.

44:17.696 --> 44:20.032
How is that important?

44:20.115 --> 44:22.743
We're on the same team.
Where's the team spirit?

44:30.250 --> 44:31.210
Look.

44:31.794 --> 44:33.671
You disgusting pig.

44:36.507 --> 44:38.967
-Look at this.
-What? Really?

44:39.551 --> 44:41.887
That's disgusting.

44:41.970 --> 44:44.515
CHAT
MUNHAK VILLAGE PLANNING TEAM ONE

44:44.598 --> 44:45.849
LEE YEO-REUM
PHOTO

44:48.185 --> 44:50.229
MANAGER CHOI JI-WON:
COME THE LOVER HOTEL, ROOM 802

44:50.312 --> 44:52.272
YEO-REUM: I'M SORRY, MR. CHOI.
I DON'T THINK I CAN DO THIS

44:58.654 --> 45:00.239
Hey, Mr. Choi!

46:46.470 --> 46:47.638
This feels great.

46:58.565 --> 47:01.610
From this moment on,
I'm not going to do anything.

47:02.402 --> 47:04.112
I'm going on a strike from life.

47:49.783 --> 47:54.037
"We may fall at times
but we're never defeated."

47:54.621 --> 47:58.417
All right, I'll live however I want here.
No more walking on eggshells.

48:00.919 --> 48:02.170
So obnoxious.

48:02.254 --> 48:05.924
How drunk do you have to be
to fall asleep at the library?

48:06.008 --> 48:07.509
-I'm sorry.
-I accept your apology.

48:08.385 --> 48:10.596
You can always leave
when you can't take it anymore.

48:10.679 --> 48:13.056
I have nothing more to lose.

48:13.140 --> 48:15.851
I'll live a life that I won't regret.

48:15.934 --> 48:17.561
I can do it!

48:17.644 --> 48:20.731
Subtitle translation by: Jea-Heon Chung
